      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/gandys_beach_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The community sits on a one‑mile stretch of undeveloped shoreline backed by tidal marshes and intertidal mud flats.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/gandys_beach_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Since 1930, the beach has retreated nearly 500 feet, a loss driven by storm surges and rising sea levels.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2,
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/gandys_beach_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The 2,485‑acre Gandy’s Beach Preserve, managed by The Nature Conservancy, protects salt marshes and supports birdwatching year‑round.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/gandys_beach_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Oyster reef breakwaters and coir logs have been installed along the shore to slow erosion and build resilience against climate change.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9,
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/gandys_beach_new_jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Gandys Beach Road runs from Route 643 westward to the bay, giving residents direct access to the waterfront and the surrounding marshlands.",
